== 3. Nc3 ==
A natural move, White develops a their queen's knight to control the centre. At the moment White's options are still open and they may choose whether to play in the modern way with g3 and Bg2, or in the traditional way with e3 and Be2. 

[[/3...Nf6|'''3...Nf6''']] is the main move here, usually followed by 4...Bg7, or in the order '''3...Bg7''' followed by  4...Nf3. White may continue with Nf3, g3, etc, or with the aggressive 4. h4! intending h5 and h6 if possible, though this attack doesn't work as well as if White had tried it on turn turn.

An unusual option, which Black enabled by having played 2...g6 before developing their knight, is [[/3...Nh6|'''3...Nh6!?''']], the '''Bladel variation'''.  

